When it comes to carbs and diabetes, there are so many conflicting views
flying around in the media you could be forgiven for being confused.
We're here to help translate all the evidence into practical advice, explain
how carbs affect your diabetes and the role they play in your overall health.
Carbs are our main source of energy, and provide nutrients for a healthy,
balanced diet. The carbs you eat and drink – including potatoes, rice and
pasta – are broken down into glucose (blood sugar), which is then used to keep
Someone is diagnosed with diabetes every two minutes. Your donation can change
